data.database_description: The database schema describes a retail system for a department store chain, encompassing various entities such as customers, suppliers, products, and staff. It tracks customer orders, product inventory, supplier relationships, and employee assignments across different departments. The schema includes detailed address information for customers and suppliers, and it manages the hierarchical structure of department stores and their departments.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each address.
Detailed description of the address including street, city, state, and zip code.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores address details for various entities such as customers and suppliers.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each employee.
Gender of the employee, represented as a single character (e.g., 'M' for male, 'F' for female).
Name of the employee.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about employees working in the department stores.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a supplier.
Name of the supplier.
Phone number for contacting the supplier.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about suppliers, including their name and contact phone number.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each department store chain.
Name of the department store chain.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains information about different department store chains.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a customer.
Code representing the payment method used by the customer.
A unique code assigned to each customer.
Name of the customer.
Primary address of the customer.
Phone number of the customer.
Email address of the customer.

Identifier linking to the Addresses table to get address details.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a customer.
Unique identifier for an address.
Start date of the address validity period.
End date of the address validity period.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores address history for customers, linking customers to their addresses over time.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each order.
Identifier linking the order to a specific customer.
Status of the order (e.g., Completed, New, PartFilled).
Date and time when the order was placed.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about customer orders including order status and date.

Name of the department store.
